Discover the latest updates and upcoming features in Azure AI Foundry Agent services. Guided Yoga Session for Well-Being and Giving

Event Overview

We invite you to join us for a guided yoga session designed to rejuvenate your body and mind. This session is focused on promoting mental health and overall well-being, while also supporti

body.content:
Guided Yoga Session for Well-Being and Giving

Event Overview

We invite you to join us for a guided yoga session designed to rejuvenate your body and mind. This session is focused on promoting mental health and overall well-being, while also supporting our organization's Give goals. The event welcomes participants who wish to attend either in person or virtually, ensuring that everyone can be included regardless of their location. This session will be led by fellow FTE, Serena Allendorfer, a Senior Product Manager in M365 supporting SOX compliance and regulatory execution for E+D. Outside of Microsoft, she is also a certified yoga instructor and leads classes in the Seattle community. 

How to Participate

Whether you choose to join onsite at B31/Whistler (MPR room in Cafe 31) or online, all are encouraged to take part. Please bring a yoga mat to ensure your comfort during the session. Feel free to invite a friend to share in this refreshing experience.

Support Our Cause

As part of our commitment to giving back, we encourage you to make a donation to our selected nonprofit organization by visiting: https://aka.ms/Give-Yoga2025

Suggested donation: $25

Alternatively, you may choose to support a nonprofit that holds personal significance to you. Your generosity will help make a positive impact in the community.

Take a Moment for Yourself

This is a wonderful opportunity to pause, engage in mindful movement, and support a meaningful cause. We hope to see you there as we come together to refresh our bodies and minds.

body.content:
M365 Core Give Event | Online Career Mentoring


Join us as we partner with CareerVillage to help provide career advice and mentorship to underrepresented youth.

To participate in this event, please follow these steps:
  1. Sign up at M365 Core Event
  2. Go to CareerVillage and sign up with your LinkedIn account or email. Please use a personal email address. 
  3. Create a profile listing the areas you're skilled in and can provide information about.
  4. Start browsing the site by topic and begin answering questions.

CareerVillage is much like an online forum where you'll be responding to questions about what kind of classes they should take, what they should major in, and more.

  

If you have any questions, please reach out to Julie Fears.

value.subject: From Kernel & AutoGen to the new Agent Framework
value.bodyPreview:
Alex Blanton, Alexandra Savelieva, Jason Virtue, Jorge Garcia Ximenez and Mark Tabladillo invite you to:
From Kernel & AutoGen to the new Agent Framework
Speakers
Elijah Straight, Takuto Higuchi & Amy Boyd

Tues, Oct 14
09:00 AM - 10:00 AM
Pacific

body.content:
Alex Blanton, Alexandra Savelieva, Jason Virtue, Jorge Garcia Ximenez and Mark Tabladillo invite you to:
From Kernel & AutoGen to the new Agent Framework
Speakers
Elijah Straight, Takuto Higuchi & Amy Boyd
 
Tues, Oct 14
09:00 AM - 10:00 AM
Pacific Time

 
Join the Meeting

Semantic Kernel and AutoGen have each built passionate developer communities — one focused on enterprise stability and connectors, the other on research-driven multi-agent collaboration. Now, with the launch of Microsoft Agent Framework, these two streams come together into a single, open-source SDK and runtime for building the next generation of multi-agent systems.

In this session, we’ll walk through the product messaging and positioning for Microsoft Agent Framework, show demos in action, and give a clear view of the migration path for existing Semantic Kernel and AutoGen projects. We’ll also cover how Microsoft Agent Framework integrates with Azure AI Foundry for enterprise-scale hosting and monitoring, and how the roadmap aligns with Microsoft 365 Agents SDK to create one unified developer stack.

This session will cover:
  1. Why Microsoft Agent Framework matters: the unification of innovation + enterprise readiness.
  2. Core pillars: interoperability (MCP, A2A, OpenAPI), research-to-production pipeline, developer-driven OSS, and enterprise-grade readiness.
  3. Demo highlights of orchestration patterns, observability, and Foundry integration.
  4. Migration guidance for Semantic Kernel and AutoGen customers, with sample code.

Reminders:

value.bodyPreview:
Goal: Align on current status, blockers, and rollout plans for Prepare.AI features across Meeting Prep and IDA. This meeting will be recorded and happens every other week.

[5m] PMs & EMs will summarize recent decisions, pivots and other communications

body.content:
Goal: Align on current status, blockers, and rollout plans for Prepare.AI features across Meeting Prep and IDA. This meeting will be recorded and happens every other week.


[5m] PMs & EMs will summarize recent decisions, pivots and other communications for Prepare.AI visibility and alignment. 

We will then follow this agenda for each crew, led by an IC DRI that each crew designates. Don't prepare slides and instead share your screen to walk us through the source of truth directly (e.g. ADO, app, dashboards, scorecards).
We'll follow this order:
    • IDA [15m]
    • Meeting Prep Canvas [15m]
    • Meeting Prep Chat [15m]
Agenda for each crew to present:
  • Feature Status & Rollout Planning
    • Share current progress, blockers, and rollout timelines
    • Share readiness for upcoming integrations (full-screen form, model changes, etc)
    • Share deliverables in the next two weeks
  • Experimentation & Evaluation
    • Review telemetry and deployment status for key components across environments (SDF, MSIT, etc.).
  • Prompt Tuning & Performance Insights
    • Recent prompt tuning updates and performance impacts including SEVAL and SAT/DSAT ratio.
  • Engineering Readiness & Integration Planning
    • Share updates from partners and stakeholders (MSAI, Calendar Form, HIVE etc)
  • Telemetry & Tracking Enhancements
    • Confirm any changes to telemetry schema and tracking mechanisms.
15m goes by quickly, prepare your comments to be succinct and convey the most relevant information. Summarize findings and topics in the meeting then share the details or links in the chat during the meeting. Use the meeting chat anytime to share real time updates, like flight progressions and new experiments to try - or to ask questions.
